Predict the output of the following pseudocode when called with n = 3:
```
function recurse(n):
    if n == 0:
        print(0)
    else:
        print(n)
        recurse(n - 1)
```

Fill in the missing condition in the recursive Fibonacci function:
```
function fib(n):
    if ____:
        return n
    return fib(n-1) + fib(n-2)
```

Fill in the missing line for binary search recursion:
```
function binarySearch(arr, low, high, key):
    if low > high:
        return -1
    mid = (low + high) / 2
    if arr[mid] == key:
        return mid
    else if arr[mid] > key:
        return ____
    else:
        return binarySearch(arr, mid+1, high, key)
```

Which recursion technique is used to solve the Towers of Hanoi problem?
```
function hanoi(n, source, target, auxiliary) {
    if (n == 1) {
        move disk from source to target
    } else {
        hanoi(n-1, source, auxiliary, target)
        move disk from source to target
        hanoi(n-1, auxiliary, target, source)
    }
}
```

Fill the missing base case for recursive computation of the nth Fibonacci number:
```
function fib(n) {
    if (___) {
        return n
    }
    return fib(n-1) + fib(n-2)
}
```

Predict the output of this recursive function:
```
function factorial(n) {
    if (n == 1) {
        return 1
    } else {
        return n * factorial(n-1)
    }
}
```
Call: factorial(5)

Which of the following is a direct recursion?
```
function directRec(n) {
    if (n == 0) return;
    directRec(n-1);
}
```

Fill the missing recursive call for sum of array elements:
```
function sum(A, n) {
    if (n == 0) return 0;
    return A[n-1] + ___;
}
```

Predict the output of this recursive function:
```
function reverse(S) {
    if (S.length == 0) return S;
    return reverse(S.slice(1)) + S[0];
}
```
Call: reverse('abc')

Which recursion pattern is used in depth-first search (DFS) of a graph?
```
function dfs(v) {
    mark v as visited
    for each neighbor u of v:
        if u not visited:
            dfs(u)
}
```

Fill the missing base case for recursive minimum in array:
```
function minArr(A, n) {
    if (n == 1) return A[0];
    return Math.min(A[n-1], ___);
}
```

Predict the output of this recursive function:
```
function countdown(n) {
    if (n == 0) return;
    console.log(n);
    countdown(n-1);
}
```
Call: countdown(3)

Which technique is used to avoid redundant recursive calls in dynamic programming?
```
function fib(n, memo) {
    if (n <= 1) return n;
    if (memo[n]) return memo[n];
    memo[n] = fib(n-1, memo) + fib(n-2, memo);
    return memo[n];
}
```
